### Legacy OxCGRT dataset

The data in this repo takes the format used from 25 April 2020-20 June 2022
The OxCGRT implemented a new data structure on 20 June 2022.  The following ten indicators were split into separate variables for non-vaccinated(NV) people and vaccinated (V) people where policies differ between these groups: C1, C2, C3, C4, C5, C6, C7, C8, H6 and H8. If there is no differentiated policy in place, we report a single variable for everyone(E). Four versions of the Stringency Index, Government Response Index, and Containment and Health index are now published; Non-Vaccinated, Vaccinated, Population Weighted Average, and Average.
This folder contains the legacy data that was in place before the data structure change on 20 June 2022. 
OxCGRT_2XXX LEGACY is the full dataset, as of 20 June 2022
OxCGRT_XXXXx_withnotes LEGACY is the full dataset, as of 20 June 2022
the /timeseries folder contains the same data but in .xlsx and .csv timeseries format.
This old data structure is described in V13 of our working paper, also archived in this folder.
For those still wishing to use this data structure, these files will continue to be updated. Data users should note that this reports the value applying to Everyone, or Non-vaccinated people (the most stringent policy in place) if differentiated policies remain, and does not take into account the less stringent policies applying to vaccinated people.
